p%3ENASA's%20distant%20Voyager%202%20probe%20has%20sent%20a%20%26quot%3Bheartbeat%26quot%3B%20signal%20to%20Earth%20after%20mission%20control%20mistakenly%20cut%20contact%2C%20the%20US%20space%20agency%20said%20Tuesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELaunched%20in%201977%20to%20explore%20the%20outer%20planets%20and%20serve%20as%20a%20beacon%20of%20humanity%20to%20the%20wider%20universe%2C%20it%20is%20currently%20more%20than%2012.3%20billion%20miles%20(19.9%20billion%20kilometers)%20from%20our%20planet%20--%20well%20beyond%20the%20solar%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20series%20of%20planned%20commands%20sent%20to%20Voyager%202%20on%20July%2021%20%26quot%3Binadvertently%20caused%20the%20antenna%20to%20point%20two%20degrees%20away%20from%20Earth%2C%26quot%3B%20NASA's%20Jet%20Propulsion%20Laboratory%20(JPL)%20said%20in%20a%20recent%20update.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20left%20it%20unable%20to%20transmit%20data%20or%20receive%20commands%20to%20its%20mission%20control%20--%20a%20situation%20that%20was%20not%20expected%20to%20be%20resolved%20until%20it%20conducted%20an%20automated%20re-orientation%20maneuver%20on%20October%2015.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20on%20Tuesday%2C%20Voyager%20project%20manager%20Suzanne%20Dodd%20told%20AFP%20the%20team%20enlisted%20the%20help%20of%20the%20Deep%20Space%20Network%20--%20an%20international%20array%20of%20giant%20radio%20antennas%2C%20plus%20a%20few%20that%20orbit%20Earth%20--%20in%20a%20last-ditch%20effort%20to%20re-establish%20contact%20sooner.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20their%20surprise%2C%20%26quot%3Bthis%20was%20successful%20in%20that%20we%20see%20the%20'heartbeat'%20signal%20from%20the%20spacecraft%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BSo%20we%20know%20the%20spacecraft%20is%20alive%20and%20operating.%20This%20buoyed%20our%20spirits.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3EMission%20Update!%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnThe%20Deep%20Space%20Network%20has%20picked%20up%20a%20carrier%20signal%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FNASAVoyager%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3E%40NASAVoyager%3C%2Fa%3E%202%2C%20letting%20us%20know%20that%20the%20spacecraft%20is%20in%20good%20health.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2FyhNIpjtY12%5C%22%3Ehttps%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2FyhNIpjtY12%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%E2%80%94%20NASA%20Sun%20%26amp%3B%20Space%20(%40NASASun)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FNASASun%2Fstatus%2F1686121118577369088%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EJuly%2031%2C%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20team%20is%20%26quot%3Bnow%20generating%20a%20new%20command%20to%20attempt%20to%20point%20the%20spacecraft%20antenna%20toward%20Earth%2C%26quot%3B%20Dodd%20added%2C%20although%20she%20said%20there%20is%20only%20a%20%26quot%3Blow%20probability%26quot%3B%20it%20will%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20given%20October%2015%20is%20a%20long%20way%20away%2C%20NASA%20will%20keep%20trying%20to%20send%20up%20these%20commands.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGolden%20Record%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20JPL%20built%20and%20operates%20Voyager%20spacecraft%2C%20the%20missions%20are%20now%20part%20of%20the%20NASA%20Heliophysics%20System%20Observatory.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EVoyager%202%20left%20the%20protective%20magnetic%20bubble%20provided%20by%20the%20Sun%2C%20called%20the%20heliosphere%2C%20in%20December%202018%2C%20and%20is%20currently%20traveling%20through%20the%20space%20between%20the%20stars.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBefore%20leaving%20our%20solar%20system%2C%20it%20explored%20Jupiter%20and%20Saturn%2C%20and%20became%20the%20first%20and%20so%20far%20only%20spacecraft%20to%20visit%20Uranus%20and%20Neptune.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EVoyager%201%20was%20mankind's%20first%20spacecraft%20to%20enter%20the%20interstellar%20medium%2C%20in%202012%2C%20and%20is%20currently%20almost%2015%20billion%20miles%20from%20Earth.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBoth%20Voyager%20spacecraft%20carry%20%26quot%3BGolden%20Records%26quot%3B%20--%2012-inch%2C%20gold-plated%20copper%20disks%20intended%20to%20convey%20the%20story%20of%20our%20world%20to%20extraterrestrials.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20include%20a%20map%20of%20our%20solar%20system%2C%20a%20piece%20of%20uranium%20that%20serves%20as%20a%20radioactive%20clock%20allowing%20recipients%20to%20date%20the%20spaceship's%20launch%2C%20and%20symbolic%20instructions%20that%20convey%20how%20to%20play%20the%20record.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20contents%20of%20the%20record%2C%20selected%20for%20NASA%20by%20a%20committee%20chaired%20by%20legendary%20astronomer%20Carl%20Sagan%2C%20include%20encoded%20images%20of%20life%20on%20Earth%2C%20as%20well%20as%20music%20and%20sounds%20that%20can%20be%20played%20using%20an%20included%20stylus.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20now%2C%20the%20Voyagers%20continue%20to%20transmit%20back%20scientific%20data%2C%20though%20their%20power%20banks%20are%20expected%20to%20be%20eventually%20depleted%2C%20sometime%20after%202025.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20will%20then%20continue%20to%20wander%20the%20Milky%20Way%2C%20potentially%20for%20eternity%2C%20in%20silence.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690910100000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-08%2Fdpgnd6go_nasa-voyager-2-probe_625x300_01_August_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fin-good-health-nasa-hears-from-voyager-2-probe-after-brief-blackout-4259981%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22NASA's%20distant%20Voyager%202%20probe%20has%20signaled%20it%20is%20in%20%26quot%3Bgood%20health%26quot%3B%20after%20mission%20control%20mistakenly%20cut%20contact%20for%20several%20days%2C%20the%20US%20space%20agency%20said%20in%20its%20latest%20update.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2