C%20only%20an%20introduction%20was%20held%20and%20not%20a%20debate%20on%20it.%20It%20is%20our%20right%20to%20oppose%20the%20introduction%20and%20five%20to%20six%20members%20of%20the%20opposition%20tried%20to%20oppose%20it%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAlthough%2C%20one%20of%20the%20parties%20from%20the%20opposition%20supported%20the%20government.%20Others%20said%20that%20it%20is%20illegal%20and%20that%20the%20government%20is%20taking%20unconstitutional%20actions%26quot%3B%2C%20added%20Shashi%20Tharoor.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENotably%2C%20the%20bill%20to%20replace%20the%20ordinance%20for%20control%20of%20services%20in%20Delhi%20was%20introduced%20in%20Lok%20Sabha%20today.%20The%20controversial%20bill%20aims%20to%20replace%20an%20ordinance%20that%20granted%20the%20Centre%20control%20over%20Delhi's%20bureaucrats%2C%20thereby%20overriding%20a%20Supreme%20Court%20ruling%20favouring%20the%20elected%20government's%20authority%20in%20transfers%20and%20appointments.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMinister%20of%20State%20for%20Home%20Nityanand%20Rai%20introduced%20the%20Government%20of%20National%20Capital%20Territory%20of%20Delhi%20(Amendment)%20Bill%2C%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOpposition%20members%20including%20Adhir%20Ranjan%20Chowdhury%2C%20NK%20Premachandran%20and%20Shashi%20Tharoor%20opposed%20the%20introduction%20of%20the%20bill.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20rise%20to%20oppose%20the%20introduction%20of%20the%20bill%20as%20the%20bill%20vindicates%20the%20outrageous%20infringement%20of%20this%20govt%20upon%20the%20territory%20of%20the%20state.%20It%20is%20designed%20of%20digging%20up%20a%20graveyard%20for%20cooperative%20federalism.%20The%20state%20has%20rights%20over%20the%20subject%20centre%20is%20overriding%20powers%2C%26quot%3B%20Adhir%20Ranjan%20Chowdhury%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERevolutionist%20Socialist%20Party%20MP%20NK%20Premachandran%20questioned%20the%20legislative%20competence%20of%20Lok%20Sabha%20over%20the%20bill.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20is%20no%20meaning%20of%20government%20in%20delhi%20if%20this%20bill%20gets%20passed.%20It%20is%20taking%20away%20legislative%20powers%20from%20the%20elected%20government%20through%20bureaucrats.%20It%20is%20overriding%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAIMIM%20MP%20Asaduddin%20Owaisi%20said%20that%20this%20bill%20is%20violating%20multiple%20provisions%20of%20the%20constitution.%26quot%3BIt%20is%20a%20violation%20of%20Article%20123.%20It%20is%20violating%20the%20separation%20of%20powers%20theory.%20There%20is%20no%20legislative%20competence.%20I%20demand%20a%20division%20of%20votes%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERejecting%20the%20contentions%20of%20opposition%20members%2C%20Home%20Minister%20Amit%20Shah%20said%20that%20Constitution%20has%20given%20the%20House%20power%20to%20pass%20any%20law%20regarding%20Delhi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20judgement%20has%20clarified%20that%20parliament%20can%20bring%20any%20law%20regarding%20Delhi%20and%20the%20opposition%20parties%20were%20opposing%20its%20introduction%20for%20political%20considerations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bill%20empowers%20the%20Central%20Government%20to%20make%20rules%20in%20connection%20with%20the%20affairs%20of%20the%20Government%20of%20the%20National%20Capital%20Territory%20of%20Delhi%20including%20the%20functions%2C%20terms%20and%20other%20conditions%20of%20service%20of%20officers%20and%20employees.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Centre%20on%20May%2019%20introduced%20the%20Ordinance%20for%20control%20of%20services%20in%20Delhi.%20The%20ordinance%20was%20introduced%20days%20after%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20order%20on%20the%20issue.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690909500000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-08%2Fcpr73