%22title%22%3A%22How%20an%20Entrepreneur%20is%20Closing%20the%20Loan%20Gap%20for%20Rural%20Women%2C%20Helping%20Thousands%20Start%20Businesses%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EK%20Priya%20and%20her%20husband%2C%20residents%20of%20Tirupati%E2%80%99s%20Tirumala%20Nagar%2C%20sold%20flowers%20on%20a%20pushcart%20to%20earn%20a%20living.%20They%20have%20two%20two%20boys%2C%20one%20in%20Class%2010%20and%20the%20other%20in%20Class%209.%20To%20save%20up%20for%20their%20college%20education%2C%20Priya%20wanted%20to%20rent%20a%20shop%20to%20sell%20flowers.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20even%20aware%20that%20someone%20like%20me%20could%20get%20a%20loan.%20I%20didn%E2%80%99t%20know%20who%20to%20approach%20or%20how%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20recalls.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESimilar%20was%20the%20case%20of%20Barathi%2C%20who%20runs%20a%20milk%20business%20from%20Tirupati%2C%20who%20recalls%20having%20to%20jump%20through%20hoops%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F296115%2Fteenagers-startup-finance4teens-educate-kids-globally-on-banking-financial-literacy%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eget%20a%20loan%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%E2%80%9CI%20run%20a%20milk%20shop%20and%20needed%20a%20loan%20to%20expand.%20I%20had%20to%20make%20multiple%20visits%20to%20get%20my%20loan%20sanctioned%20earlier.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20India%2C%20there%20is%20a%20large%20gender%20gap%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20access%20to%20credit.%20A%202022%20report%20by%20the%20%3Cem%3EInternational%20Finance%20Corporation%20(IFC)%20%3C%2Fem%3Eestimates%20a%20Rs%20836%20billion%20credit%20demand%20by%20women-owned%20very%20small%20enterprises.%20Meanwhile%2C%20a%20%3Cem%3EProtium%20%3C%2Fem%3Ereport%20further%20states%20that%20there%20is%20a%C2%A0%20credit%20gap%20of%20%24158%20billion%20for%20women-led%20businesses%20as%20a%20whole.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20women%20like%20Barathi%20and%20Priya%2C%20India%20P2P%2C%20a%20peer-to-peer%20lending%20platform%20run%20by%20Mumbai-based%20entrepreneur%20Neha%20Juneja%20has%20been%20a%20boon.%20Barathi%20notes%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20received%20a%20pamphlet%20and%20I%20called%20them.%20An%20officer%20came%2C%20and%20after%20verifying%20the%20details%2C%20the%20loan%20was%20disbursed%20in%20a%20day.%E2%80%9D%20Similar%20was%20the%20case%20of%20Priya%2C%20who%20availed%20a%20loan%20of%20Rs%2030%2C000%20in%20March%202023%2C%20and%20was%20successfully%20able%20to%20set%20up%20her%20flower%20shop.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENeha%20says%20that%20her%20introduction%20to%20microfinance%20happened%20when%20she%20was%20working%20with%20rural%20women%20at%20Greenway%20Grameen%20Infra%2C%20which%20manufactures%20biomass%20cook%20stoves.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20travelled%20to%20several%20villages%20and%20saw%20the%20thriving%20self-help%20groups%20(SHG)%20credit%20culture.%20I%20discovered%20that%20they%20are%20a%20great%20asset%20class%20and%20pay%20back%20loans%20on%20time.%20I%20also%20found%20that%20they%20are%20starved%20of%20credit%20as%20conventional%20investors%20can%E2%80%99t%20make%20up%20their%20mind%20that%20rural%20women%20are%20income%20generators%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Neha%20in%20a%20conversation%20with%20%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Better%20India%3C%2Fstrong%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EClosing%20the%20credit%20gap%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20660px)%20100vw%2C%20660px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Fneha2-1690548239.jpeg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22660%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Neha%20Juneja%20started%20India%20P2P%20in%202021%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Fneha2-1690548239.jpeg%20660w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Fneha2-1690548239-300x205.jpeg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Fneha2-1690548239-500x341.jpeg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Fneha2-1690548239-150x102.jpeg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-325613%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22450%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3ENeha%20Juneja%20started%20India%20P2P%20in%202021%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENeha%20launched%20India%20P2P%20in%202021.%20The%20company%20is%20%E2%80%9Can%20attempt%20to%20unlock%20more%20capital%20for%20women%20borrowers%2C%20especially%20in%20rural%20areas%2C%20for%20businesses%20or%20purchase%20of%20productive%20assets%20like%20washing%20machines%20or%20refrigerators%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%C2%A0%20By%20eliminating%20the%20middleman%2C%20i.e%2C%20the%20bank%2C%20this%20platform%20gets%20the%20capital%20for%20these%20loans%20by%20letting%20investors%20invest%20directly.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20do%20so%2C%20they%20have%20built%20a%20technology%20platform%20that%20enables%20risk%20and%20portfolio%20management.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9COur%20retail%20investors%20invest%20directly%20in%20the%20women%20borrowers%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F304454%2Ftwo-friends-climate-tech-startup-climes-helps-neutralise-carbon-footprint%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eour%20technology%20platform%3C%2Fa%3E%20ends%20up%20reducing%20credit%20cost%20for%20the%20borrower.%20The%20platform%20splits%20your%20investment%20across%2010%20borrowers%20from%2010%20geographies%2C%20mitigating%20the%20risk.%20It%20has%20various%20parameters%20to%20split%20your%20capital%2C%E2%80%9D%20adds%20Neha.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20have%20built%20an%20app%20for%20borrowers%2C%20agents%2C%20and%20an%20underwriting%20module.%20Neha%20says%20that%20they%20are%20able%20to%20give%20about%2015-16%20per%20cent%20return%20to%20their%2018%2C000%20investors%2C%20and%20have%20disbursed%2010%2C000%20loans.%20India%20P2P%20partners%20with%20last%20mile%20organisations%20like%20Seva%20Mandir%20and%20UNDP%20in%20pockets%20across%20the%20country.%20These%20regions%20include%20Nagaland%2C%20all%20five%20southern%20states%2C%20and%20Maharashtra%2C%20to%20name%20a%20few%2C%20to%20ensure%20that%20women%20everywhere%20are%20able%20to%20access%20credit.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20work%20with%20NGOs%20and%20microfinance%20institutions%20(MFIs).%20Most%20loans%20are%20given%20to%20women%20who%20are%20part%20of%20SHGs%2C%20which%20is%20a%20powerful%20structure%20for%20accountability.%20They%20attend%20the%20weekly%20group%20meetings%20of%20SHGs%20to%20ensure%20that%20those%20who%20need%20loans%20are%20given%20loans.%20Our%20loan%20officers%20visit%20the%20borrower%E2%80%99s%20place%20of%20work%20for%20due%20diligence.%20Once%20they%20are%20satisfied%2C%20the%20loans%20are%20disbursed%2C%E2%80%9D%20explains%20the%20CEO.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMost%20loans%20disbursed%20fall%20between%20Rs%2040%2C000%20and%20Rs%2050%2C000%20on%20an%20average.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EIndian%20women%20have%20higher%20credit%20scores%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Fwomen-india-p2p-1690548462.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22India%20P2P%20caters%20majorly%20to%20women%20borrowers%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Fwomen-india-p2p-1690548462.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Fwomen-india-p2p-1690548462-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Fwomen-india-p2p-1690548462-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Fwomen-india-p2p-1690548462-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Fwomen-india-p2p-1690548462-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-325622%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EIndia%20P2P%20caters%20majorly%20to%20women%20borrowers%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENeha%20notes%20that%2096%25%20of%20India%20P2P%E2%80%99s%20borrowers%20are%20women.%20The%20biggest%20challenge%20has%20been%20building%20awareness%20about%20the%20fact%20that%20%E2%80%9Crural%20women%20are%20India%E2%80%99s%20best%20asset%20class%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThere%20is%20a%20very%20low%20probability%20that%20your%20income%20will%20be%20affected.%20Women%20are%20the%20best%20asset%20class%20and%20best%20borrowers.%20They%20default%20less.%20The%20default%20rate%20of%20women%20in%20microfinance%20in%20the%20sub%20Rs%201%20lakh%20is%20less%20than%201%25%20in%20India.%20Yet%2C%20they%20don%E2%80%99t%20get%20loans%2C%E2%80%9D%20adds%20Neha.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20a%20report%20by%20Transunion%20CIBIL%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F316961%2Fbengaluru-entrepreneur-platform-find-jobs-for-women-after-career-maternity-break-herkey%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewomen%20have%20a%20higher%20credit%20score%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20720%20on%20an%20average%20compared%20to%20709%20for%20men.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWomen%20have%20a%20high%20sense%20of%20responsibility.%20They%20pay%20back%20on%20time%20without%20follow%20ups.%20They%20want%20their%20family%20to%20thrive%20and%20prosper.%20Yet%2C%20the%20reject%20rates%20are%20higher%20for%20women%20borrowers.%20They%20are%20asked%20for%20NOCs%20from%20their%20husbands%20or%20fathers%20even%20when%20they%20are%20financially%20independent%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Neha.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20says%20that%20there%20is%20a%20very%20high%20demand%20for%20loans%20by%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F310452%2Fbengaluru-student-financial-independence-portal-for-domestic-workers-finwin-anaya-jethanandani%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewomen%20who%20run%20small%20businesse%3C%2Fa%3Es.%20She%20is%20on%20a%20mission%20to%20unlock%20capital%20worth%20billions%20of%20dollars%20for%20these%20women.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIf%20India%20has%20to%20become%20a%20prosperous%20and%20more%20equitable%20country%2C%20she%20needs%20to%20give%20women%20more%20credit.%20These%20loans%20help%20families%20overcome%20poverty.%20We%20will%20help%20as%20many%20women%20as%20possible%20to%20do%20so%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch5%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3ESources%3C%2Fh5%3E%5Cn%3Ch5%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fprotium.co.in%2F2023%2F01%2F09%2Fwomen-entrepreneurs-financing-gap%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DAs%2520per%25202021%2527s%2520Global%2520Findex%2Cshare%2520against%252015%2525%2520for%2520men.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EProtium%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fh5%3E%5Cn%3Ch5%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fnews%2Feconomy%2Findicators%2Fwomen-more-credit-conscious-than-men-report%2Farticleshow%2F81389164.cms%3Ffrom%3Dmdr%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98Women%20more%20credit%20conscious%20than%20men%3A%20Report%E2%80%99%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20Gayatri%20Nayak%20for%20Economic%20Times%2C%20Published%20on%2008%20March%2C%202021%3C%2Fh5%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690549022000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Fneha2-1690548239.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F%3Fp%3D325587%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Mumbai%20entrepreneur%20Neha%20Juneja%20runs%20India%20P2P%2C%20a%20unique%20lending%20platform%20that%20is%20aiming%20to%20close%20the%20credit%20gap%20for%20women%20entrepreneurs%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20rural%20regions.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22Sowmya%20Mani%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A14%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F325587%2Fmumbai-entrepreneur-runs-lending-platform-for-rural-indian-women-loans-businesses%2F%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22From%20Prejudice%20to%20Pride%3A%20Evolving%20Representations%20of%20Disability%20in%20Cinema%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EPopular%20media%20can%20be%20a%20powerful%20facilitator%20in%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F295507%2Fdisability-inclusive-policy-at-workplaces-lessons-from-accenture%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20inculcating%20disability%20prid%3C%2Fa%3Ee%2C%20acting%20as%20a%20mode%20of%20representation%20for%20people%20with%20disabilities%20to%20see%20those%20like%20them%20included%20in%20the%20mainstream.%20However%2C%20when%20we%20look%20at%20representations%20of%20disability%2C%20we%20see%20that%20it%E2%80%99s%20either%20a%20complete%20lack%20of%20proportional%20representation%2C%20or%20portrayals%20that%20continue%20to%20be%20mostly%20stuck%20in%20outdated%20understandings%20of%20the%20subject.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20fact%2C%20when%20you%20think%20of%20word%20disability%2C%20what%20words%20pop%20up%20in%20your%20head%3F%20Is%20it%20%E2%80%98inspirational%E2%80%99%2C%20or%20%E2%80%98sad%E2%80%99%3F%20Or%20maybe%20even%20%E2%80%98inability%E2%80%99%20and%20%E2%80%98challenging%E2%80%99%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWould%20%E2%80%98pride%E2%80%99%20ever%20find%20a%20place%20on%20that%20list%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMaybe%20not%2C%20but%20it%20should.%20The%20fact%20is%20that%20millions%20across%20the%20world%20are%20proud%20of%20their%20identities%20as%20people%20with%20disabilities%2C%20and%20every%20July%20marks%20a%20whole%20month%20where%20they%20celebrate%20themselves%20%E2%80%94%20Disability%20Pride%20Month.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20cinema%2C%20a%20powerful%20tool%20to%20map%20the%20real%20world%2C%20can%20go%20a%20long%20way%20in%20encouraging%20this%20sense%20of%20pride%20and%20acceptance%20of%20diversity.%20It%20bears%20the%20responsibility%20of%20disseminating%20awareness%20and%20education%20to%20nurture%20a%20world%20that%20is%20sensitive%20to%20people%20with%20disabilities%20and%20sees%20them%20as%20people%20first%20over%20everything%20else.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%20where%20does%20cinema%20stand%20in%20this%20respect%20today%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98No%20visible%20boundaries%E2%80%99%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20first%2C%20what%20is%20Disability%20Pride%20month%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Fdisability-pride-flag-1690540782.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22disability%20pride%20flag%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Fdisability-pride-flag-1690540782.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Fdisability-pride-flag-1690540782-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Fdisability-pride-flag-1690540782-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Fdisability-pride-flag-1690540782-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Fdisability-pride-flag-1690540782-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-325551%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFirst%20observed%20in%201990%2C%20Disability%20Pride%20Month%20commemorates%20the%20passing%20of%20the%20Americans%20with%20Disabilities%20Act%20on%20July%2026%2C%201990.%20Boston%20was%20among%20the%20first%20cities%20to%20mark%20the%20occasion%2C%20and%20the%20ripples%20of%20these%20celebrations%20are%20felt%20across%20the%20world%20today%2C%20in%20a%20powerful%20force%20of%20solidarity%20that%20has%20brought%20the%20community%20together.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDisability%20Pride%20is%20an%20opportunity%20to%20shed%20the%20traditional%20narratives%20of%20ableism%20and%20societal%20stigma%20that%20have%20surrounded%20the%20disability%20discourse%20for%20way%20too%20long%2C%20and%20view%20people%20with%20disabilities%20as%20equitable%20and%20positive%20contributors%20to%20society.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDisability%20does%20not%20mean%20inability%2C%20and%20it%20is%20something%20that%20can%20happen%20to%20anyone%20anytime.%20There%E2%80%99s%20nothing%20upsetting%2C%20unfortunate%2C%20or%20inspiring%20about%20living%20the%20life%20of%20a%20person%20with%20a%20disability.%20Disability%20Pride%20is%2C%20instead%2C%20a%20chance%20to%20look%20back%20on%20one%E2%80%99s%20journey%20to%20acknowledge%20how%20far%20they%20have%20come%2C%20the%20odds%20they%20have%20traversed%2C%20and%20how%20we%20may%20mobilise%20the%20community%2C%20garner%20support%2C%20and%20instil%20belief.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EIt%20is%20important%20to%20remember%20that%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20a%20%E2%80%98one%20size%20fits%20all%E2%80%99%20phenomenon.%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJust%20as%20one%E2%80%99s%20experience%20with%20disability%20is%20subjective%2C%20so%20is%20their%20understanding%20of%20Disability%20Pride%20%E2%80%94%20it%E2%80%99s%20all%20about%20your%20lived%20experience.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAs%20a%20young%20adult%2C%20%E2%80%98Disability%20Pride%E2%80%99%20seemed%20inauthentic%20and%20more%20of%20a%20propaganda%20campaign.%20I%20have%20faced%20so%20many%20challenges%20and%20lived%20so%20many%20awkward%20moments%20as%20a%20person%20with%20a%20locomotor%20disability.%20How%20could%20I%20be%20proud%20of%20my%20disability%3F%20But%20as%20I%20grew%20older%2C%20I%20realised%20that%20it%E2%80%99s%20about%20understanding%20what%20our%20disability%20is%20to%20us%2C%20being%20comfortable%20in%20our%20own%20skin%20and%20celebrating%20our%20journey%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Kavya%2C%20a%20job%20coach%20at%20v-shesh%2C%20an%20enterprise%20that%20prepares%20organisations%20with%20disability%20inclusion.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20Anjali%20Vyas%2C%20who%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F317421%2Fhow-to-build-inclusive-workplace-navigate-blood-disorders-thalassemia-with-employers%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elives%20with%20an%20invisible%20disability%3C%2Fa%3E%20called%20Multiple%20Sclerosis%2C%20%E2%80%9CDisability%20Pride%20has%20no%20visible%20boundaries.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Fdisability-pride-parade-1690540942.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Disability%20Pride%20Parade%20Chicago%20participants%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Fdisability-pride-parade-1690540942.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Fdisability-pride-parade-1690540942-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Fdisability-pride-parade-1690540942-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Fdisability-pride-parade-1690540942-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Fdisability-pride-parade-1690540942-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-325555%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EA%20disability%20pride%20parade%20in%20Chicago%20(Wikimedia%20Commons)%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CLiving%20with%20an%20invisible%20disability%20reminds%20me%20that%20strength%20and%20pride%20come%20in%20many%20forms.%20When%20I%20was%20diagnosed%20with%20MS%2C%20things%20were%20definitely%20challenging%2C%20but%20in%20the%20face%20of%20that%20uncertainty%2C%20I%20found%20myself.%20Most%20importantly%2C%20I%20discovered%20my%20power.%20I%20am%20proud%20of%20the%20way%20I%20have%20been%20living%20with%20MS%20and%20defying%20limitations%20like%20the%20inaccessibility%2C%20ableism%20and%20the%20stigma%20around%20this%20invisible%20disability%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Anjali%2C%20a%20chemical%20engineer-turned-English%20language%20trainer%20from%20Bhandara%2C%20Maharashtra.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EWhen%20it%20comes%20to%20this%20sense%20of%20pride%2C%20why%20is%20representation%20important%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20that%2C%20let%E2%80%99s%20look%20at%20some%20earlier%20portrayals%20of%20disability%20in%20Indian%20cinema.%20How%20often%20have%20we%20seen%20that%20disability%20has%20been%20portrayed%20as%20a%20point%20of%20comic%20relief%2C%20or%20a%20punchline%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20%3Cem%3EGolmaal%20%3C%2Fem%3E(2006)%2C%20Tusshar%20Kapoor%E2%80%99s%20character%20has%20a%20speech%20impairment%2C%20and%20Paresh%20Rawal%20and%20Sushmita%20Mukherjee%E2%80%99s%20characters%20are%20portrayed%20as%20blind%20%E2%80%94%20all%20for%20gags.%20In%20%3Cem%3EMujhse%20Shaadi%20Karogi%20%3C%2Fem%3E(2004)%2C%20Kader%20Khan%E2%80%99s%20character%20is%20seen%20to%20have%20a%20%E2%80%9Cdifferent%20disability%E2%80%9D%20every%20day.%20The%20staff%20at%20his%20care%20facility%20trivialises%20it%20and%20portrays%20as%20%E2%80%9Cmake-believe%E2%80%9D%20that%20the%20character%20engages%20in.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENeedless%20to%20say%2C%20portrayals%20of%20disability%20in%20Indian%20films%20and%20other%20media%20leave%20a%20lot%20to%20be%20desired.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20may%20say%20that%20these%20are%20just%20light-hearted%20movies%20meant%20for%20entertainment.%20But%20it%20is%20integral%20to%20acknowledge%20that%20we%20are%20at%20a%20point%20in%20history%20where%20there%20is%20a%20greater%20attempt%20to%20look%20beyond%20the%20myths%20and%20stereotypes%2C%20and%20understand%20disability%20for%20what%20it%20truly%20is.%20Reducing%20it%20to%20a%20punchline%20reinforces%20existing%20stereotypes%20in%20the%20minds%20of%20the%20viewers.%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20popular%20trope%20that%20a%20number%20of%20filmmakers%20have%20engaged%20in%20is%20the%20infantilisation%20of%20people%20with%20disabilities.%20This%20can%20be%20seen%20in%20popular%20movies%20like%20%3Cem%3EKoi%20Mil%20Gaya%3C%2Fem%3E%20(2003)%20and%20%3Cem%3EBarfi%20%3C%2Fem%3E(2012).%20Here%2C%20adults%20with%20disabilities%20are%20portrayed%20as%20%E2%80%9Cinnocent%E2%80%9D%20or%20even%20childlike%20in%20their%20actions%2C%20speech%2C%20or%20capabilities.%20This%20contributes%20to%20the%20belief%20that%20persons%20with%20disabilities%20always%20need%20to%20be%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F253449%2Fcoronavirus-resources-for-persons-with-disabilities-caregivers-covid-19-online-support-groups-job-portals-companionship-mental-health-nimhans-india-div200%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eunder%20the%20care%20of%20someone%20%3C%2Fa%3Eand%20can%E2%80%99t%20be%20independent%2C%20the%20way%20one%20one%20would%20be%20with%20a%20child.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Fdisability-in-cinema-1690541530.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Fdisability-in-cinema-1690541530.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Fdisability-in-cinema-1690541530-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Fdisability-in-cinema-1690541530-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Fdisability-in-cinema-1690541530-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Fdisability-in-cinema-1690541530-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-325558%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EWhile%20disability%20is%20caricaturized%20in%20Golmaal%2C%20Koi%20Mil%20Gayaa%20uses%20it%20to%20infantilize%20the%20main%20character.%20%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThen%20there%E2%80%99s%20the%20opposite%20route%20of%20morbidity.%20In%20%3Cem%3EGuzaarish%3C%2Fem%3E%20(2010)%2C%20we%20see%20Hrithik%20Roshan%E2%80%99s%20character%20insisting%20on%20how%20he%E2%80%99d%20rather%20die%20than%20live%20a%20long%20happy%20life%20as%20a%20person%20with%20a%20disability.%20He%20has%20a%20promising%20career%2C%20and%20a%20supportive%20community.%20Yet%20he%20is%20unable%20to%20make%20meaning%20of%20his%20life.%20Persons%20who%20have%20acquired%20a%20disability%20go%20through%20a%20whole%20course%20of%20turbulent%20emotions%2C%20ones%20that%20may%20include%20the%20feelings%20described%20above.%20Films%20like%20this%20present%20a%20rather%20morbid%20take%20and%20make%20the%20viewer%20feel%20like%20this%20is%20normal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20also%20often%20misses%20the%20mark%20is%20media%20representation%20of%20neurodiversity.%20Shows%20like%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Good%20Doctor%20%3C%2Fem%3Eand%20%3Cem%3EAtypical%20%3C%2Fem%3Erepresent%20neurodiversity%20in%20stereotypical%20ways.%20For%20instance%2C%20not%20every%20individual%20who%20is%20on%20the%20autism%20spectrum%20possesses%20savant%20skills.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20often%20goes%20untouched%20is%20the%20fact%20that%20autism%20is%20a%20spectrum%2C%20and%20that%20every%20autistic%20experience%20is%20unique%20and%20extremely%20individual-centric.%20Another%20bone%20of%20contention%20that%20affects%20the%20autistic%20community%20is%20the%20fact%20that%20such%20roles%20are%20played%20by%20allistic%20(non-autistic%20characters).%20Oftentimes%2C%20even%20the%20team%20of%20directors%20or%20writers%20is%20devoid%20of%20any%20person%20with%20autism%2C%20as%20was%20true%20in%20the%20case%20of%20Atypical%2C%20in%20which%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FAtypical%2Fstatus%2F890667170266357760%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%3Eautistic%20representation%20could%20only%20manage%20to%20find%20a%20place%20in%20one%20of%20the%20supporting%20roles%20and%20the%20social%20media%20team%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EWhere%20are%20the%20PwDs%20in%20the%20writers%E2%80%99%20rooms%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESuch%20portrayals%20of%20disability%20make%20pity%20or%20sympathy%20the%20focal%20point%20of%20disability%20and%20take%20away%20from%20the%20narrative%20of%20pride%20and%20equity.%20A%20big%20reason%20why%20the%20representation%20of%20disability%20remains%20rudimentary%20is%20that%20there%20are%20very%20few%20PwDs%20in%20the%20writer%E2%80%99s%20rooms%2C%20wearing%20the%20director%E2%80%99s%20cap%2C%20or%20even%20representing%20themselves%20on%20screen.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EResearch%20in%20the%20United%20States%20has%20shown%20that%20more%20than%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2021%2F07%2F28%2Farts%2Ftelevision%2Fdisability-representation-study-film-television.html%5C%22%3E95%25%20of%20the%20characters%20with%20disabilities%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20played%20by%20actors%20without%20disabilities.%20In%20the%20USA%2C%20there%20is%20one%20person%20with%20a%20disability%20for%20every%20four%20people%2C%20but%20only%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.respectability.org%2F2019%2F11%2Fglaad-tv-report-2019%2F%5C%22%3E3.1%20percent%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20characters%20that%20are%20shown%20on-screen%20are%20disabled.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20numbers%20are%20even%20lesser%20for%20children%20with%20disabilities%20%E2%80%94%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fseejane.org%2Fresearch-informs-empowers%2Fsee-jane-2019%2F%5C%22%3Eless%20than%20one%20percent%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Several%20studies%20also%20show%20that%20the%20industry%20is%20losing%20billions%20of%20dollars%20by%20not%20being%20inclusive%20%E2%80%94%20the%20spirit%C2%A0%20of%20the%20DEI%20(Disability%20Equality%20Indiex)%20has%20not%20yet%20seeped%20into%20the%20creative%20space.%20For%20instance%2C%20a%20research%20study%20by%20Ruderman%20Family%20Foundation%20found%20that%20Hollywood%20is%20incurring%20whopping%20losses%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Frudermanfoundation.org%2Fwhite_papers%2Fdisability-inclusion-in-movies-and-television-market-research-2019%2F%5C%22%3E%24125%20billion%20dollars%3C%2Fa%3E%20every%20year%20by%20not%20having%20authentic%20disability%20representation.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EWhere%20we%20make%20strides%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThough%20disability%20representation%20in%20mainstream%20media%20is%20still%20far%20from%20authentic%2C%20it%20has%20come%20a%20long%20way%20from%20being%20restricted%20to%20characters%20that%20garner%20a%20few%20laughs%20to%20ones%20that%20foster%20compassion%20and%20are%20a%20window%20into%20the%20life%20of%20a%20person%20with%20a%20disability.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHere%20is%20a%20list%20of%20a%20few%20recommendations%20that%20you%20can%20indulge%20in%20this%20Disability%20Pride%20Month%20with%20your%20family.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMargarita%20with%20a%20Straw%20(2014)%20%E2%80%93